Yobe State Police Command has assured people in the state of sustained efforts in the fight against crime and criminality before, during and after the Sallah festivities. The Command through its Spokesman, DSP Dungus Abdulkarim, gave the assurance in a statement issued to newsmen in Damaturu. The statement added that the State Commissioner of Police, Haruna Garba, had during the week held a meeting with Area Commanders, DPOs as well as Strategic Heads of Department where he charged them to emplace all necessary security measures with a view to ensure enabling environment for a hitch free and peaceful Eid celebrations. The Command also enjoined people in the state to be law abiding citizens, obey traffic regulations, avoid reckless driving and contribute to the existing relative peace in the state by providing useful and credible information at the nearest Police stations. It equally admonished all security personnel to be professional in carrying out their lawful duties while being mindful of the rights of citizens. “To this end, the Commissioner of Police wishes all Muslim Ummah happy and peaceful Eid celebrations and calls on all and sundry to be vigilant and security conscious”, it said.